===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant-y|carr|y|}}

#{{transitive}} To [[lift]] and bring to somewhere else; to [[transport]] by lifting.
#{{transitive}} To [[stock]] or [[supply]].
#:''The corner drugstore doesn't '''carry''' his favorite brand of aspirin.''
#{{transitive}} To [[adopt]]; [[take over]] or [[stand in]].
#:''I think I can carry Smith's work while she is out.''
#{{transitive}} {{arithmetic}} In an [[addition]], to transfer the quantity in excess of what is countable in the [[units]] in a column to the column to the left to be added there.
#:''Five and nine are fourteen; '''carry''' the one to the tens place.''
#{{transitive}} To [[have]] or [[maintain]].
#:''Always '''carry''' sufficient insurance to protect against a loss.''
#{{intransitive}} To be [[transmit]]ted; to [[travel]].
#:''The sound of the bells '''carried''' for miles on the wind.''

